The National Assembly Service Commission (NASC) has confirmed Olatunde Ojo as the substantive Clerk to the National Assembly (CNA). The appointment was contained in a statement by NASC Chairman, Ahmad Amshi. Chinedu Akabueze is the substantive Clerk to the House of Representatives. They had been in an acting capacity since July. Other confirmed appointments are Bala Yabani, Deputy Clerk to NASS; Dauda Ladan, Clerk of the Senate; Yusuf Danbatta, Secretary to NASC; Orunwase Osaze, Secretary Human Resources and Staff Development. Ademola Adebanjo is the Secretary, Legal; Ramatu Ahmad, Secretary, Research and Information; Basir Hamza, Secretary, Health Service; Sani Tambuwal, Secretary Health Services. The rest are Aimua Ehikioya, Secretary, Special Duties; Liman Sanda, Secretary, Procurement, Estate and Works; Oladoyin Suraj, Secretary, Inter-Parliamentary and Protocol; Iloba Ugochi, Deputy Clerk of Senate (Legislative). Navati Illiya is the Deputy Clerk of the Senate (Administration) and Damzariya Himidu was confirmed as Deputy Clerk of the House of Representatives. All appointments were effective September 30, except for Akabueze whose appointment would take effect from November 25.